system opens a chat interface with the AI assistant. The assistant asks
short, context-aware questions such as:

-``Do you like this current mood setup?''\\
-``Would you prefer brighter lighting or a softer scent?''

to enhance personalization. Positive or frequently accepted
configurations are treated as ``preferred examples,'' guiding future
inference in similar contexts. The AI dynamically updates user profiles
based on this data, gradually shaping individual tendencies such as
preferred lighting tone or scent strength. When conflicting prefe-rences
occur, recency-based weighting ensures that the model adapts to the
user's current lifestyle rather than outdated data.

4)Emotion and Sentiment Recognition

The NLP module analyzes the emotional tone of chat inputs to detect user
sentiment (positive, neutral, or negative). If stress or fatigue-related
language is detected (e.g., ``I'm tired,'' ``Too loud''), the system
proactively adjusts to a Relax or Comfort mood scene. This
sentiment-aware control enhances emotional intelligence and user
satisfaction.

